io.opencensus.tags.propagation

Class TagContextBinarySerializer

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.opencensus.tags.propagation.TagContextBinarySerializer

  • public abstract class TagContextBinarySerializer
extends Object
    Object for serializing and deserializing TagContexts with the binary format.

    See opencensus-specs for the specification of the cross-language binary serialization format.

      • toByteArray

        public abstract byte[] toByteArray(TagContext tags)
                            throws TagContextSerializationException
        Serializes the TagContext into the on-the-wire representation.

        This method should be the inverse of fromByteArray(byte[]).

        Parameters:
        tags - the TagContext to serialize.
        Returns:
        the on-the-wire representation of a TagContext.
        Throws:
        TagContextSerializationException - if the result would be larger than the maximum allowed serialized size.

      • fromByteArray

        public abstract TagContext fromByteArray(byte[] bytes)
                                  throws TagContextDeserializationException
        Creates a TagContext from the given on-the-wire encoded representation.

        This method should be the inverse of toByteArray(io.opencensus.tags.TagContext).

        Parameters:
        bytes - on-the-wire representation of a TagContext.
        Returns:
        a TagContext deserialized from bytes.
        Throws:
        TagContextDeserializationException - if there is a parse error, the input contains invalid tags, or the input is larger than the maximum allowed serialized size.
